<HEADLINE>
AVERAGE MONTHLY PAY FOR EXECUTIVE-LEVEL EMPLOYEES DOWN IN 2006
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Jan.  (CNA) 01/02/07  10:32:22 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
The average monthly wage for executive-level employees of
companies in Taiwan's industrial and service sectors dropped
below NT$50,000 in 2006, according to statistics released by the
Cabinet-level Directorate General of Budget, Accounting and
Statistics (DGBAS) Monday.
</P>
<P>
The statistics, compiled by the DGBAS every year between May and
June and released at year's end, show the average monthly salary
for executive-level employees in June 2006 stood at NT$47,630, a
decrease of NT$2,839 from the NT$50,469 recorded in June 2005.
</P>
<P>
The same fate befell technical employees, who saw their average
monthly pay in 2006 slashed by NT$2,819.
</P>
<P>
Faring better were personnel handling general affairs, who saw
their average monthly wage rise by NT$2,348 in 2006, while pay
for staff in charge of customer service and sales went up by
NT$2,133.
</P>
<P>
Overall, the average worker's wage in Taiwan's industrial and
service sectors in June 2006 increased a meager NT$192 to a
monthly total of NT$26,266 from the same month of 2005, according
to the statistics.
</P>
